            "title": "TSLA stock jumps 1.85% in pre-market; Elon Musk's compensation plan potentially worth $1 trillion tied to $8.5 trillion value.",
            "id": "4b3c5252-e24b-440c-8d96-e5453eba931a",
            "description": "Shares of Tesla Inc. (NASDAQ: TSLA) surged by 1.85% in pre-market trading on Friday as the company introduced a revolutionary compensation package for CEO Elon Musk, potentially valued at $1 trillion. The proposal, disclosed in a proxy filing, links Musk's compensation to challenging objectives set over the next ten years. If approved, Musk will begin receiving shares in Tesla once the company reaches a market cap of $8.5 trillion, a significant increase from its current $1 trillion valuation. The plan indicates that he would receive 12 tranches of shares, with the first being provided once Tesla's market cap hits $8.5 trillion. Check out the complete story on Benzinga.com.",
